 :tx/rationale "OBSERVER SCHEMA GAPS (from Session 034 analysis). The current :extractor/* schema captures HOW to invoke an observer but not WHAT it observes or HOW to evaluate quality. Missing fields needed for the three learning loops: (1) :extractor/source-category (Keyword) — what aspect of reality this observer measures: :category/structure, /behavior, /history, /intent, /configuration. Without this, OBSERVER-5 cannot detect cross-category coupling. (2) :extractor/expected-boundaries (String, Many) — which policy boundaries this observer's output informs. Without this, OBSERVER-4 cannot attribute F(S) changes to specific observers. (3) :extractor/observation-cost (Long) — estimated cost in milliseconds. Without this, the acquisition function cannot optimize information-gain-per-cost (the acquisition function from Bayesian optimal experimental design). (4) :extractor/composition (Ref, Many) — which other extractors this one's output combines with. Without this, the system cannot reason about observer composition (A output + B output = complete graph). These 4 fields complete the observer interface and enable the three learning loops to operate on extractor selection."
